    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The raised surface produced by supplementary warp or weft projecting from the ground of a woven textile. For the surface produced by raising the fibers on the face of the textile, use "nap."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
